mpanies to the united kingdom spain cyprus south east asia west africa cis countries the united arab emirates and the us with a background in commerce and mathematics lubert specialises in financial structuring acquisition and marketing gary shepherd cofounder and joint chairman britishborn gary shepherd has been actively involved in overseas property development since the early s after working predominantly with danny lubert the highly successful pair continued their powerful partnership by cofounding and chairing the first group previously shepherd worked in spain and south east asia consulting for major development companies such as eurodisney and the berajaya group of malaysia together with danny lubert shepherd has been pivotal in shaping the first group in dubai drawing from his strong background in developing emerging markets and innovative product design his ability to adapt to the property market’s changing demographics makes him an excellent asset to the first group rob burns chief operating officer rob burns is a graduate of pennsylvania state university where he studied business marketing and hotel  resort management his career in property development dates back to  spanning the us united kingdom europe cis africa and the middle east he has a diverse background in a wide array of disciplines including the direction of sales and marketing operations brand advertising database marketing direct mail telesales print and public relations as well as extensive interactive experience having worked with major institutions around the world burns began his journey with the first group as chief marketing officer prior to being promoted to chief operating officer mark tolner chief financial officer with over  years experience in a variety of seniorlevel business operations including shipping asset management venture capital and feature film production and distribution mark has proudly assisted in the key development of a multitude of international ventures he draws from this extensive background as chief financial officer for the first group helping to facilitate and manage our rapid growth rashad barajakly chief investment officer rashad brings a wealth of expertise to the first group drawing from a strong background in finance and investment banking in the us and dubai he held senior positions in new york and atlanta before joining difc from there he went on to assist in the launch of difx and later furthered his banking career by working with nbk capital and boutique investment companies his experience of operations and finance in both private and public companies makes him an extremely valuable asset to the first group mariano faz head of asset management mariano draws on more than  years of expertise in global hospitality and real estate markets as an mba graduate in finance from eada in barcelona he has held a number of high level positions in the hospitality industry largely in the fields of operations and business development before joining tfg asset management mariano worked as a senior consultant in dubai for one of the largest consultancy companies jones lang lasalle hotels mariano’s varied background and vast knowledge of the industry ensures he has the experience required to successfully lead the tfg asset management team deirdre mccarthybetzold head of business development  operations deirdre has spent most of her  year working life developing a career within the property sector at a managerial level her marketing background set a strong foundation for a career in business development while her postgraduate studies in interior design and architecture led to roles fitting out serviced apartment towers and residences in the region in  realising the increasing market demand for experts in property management deirdre returned to her studies and achieved an internationally accredited diploma within this field she has taken on projects and turned them into professionally managed profitable establishments often reaching 